content:
Before setting up your web form with Web-to-Case, complete these steps:

Choose case fields to include in your web form. Create an email template for automated notifications sent to customers.
TIP: Use the Service Setup Assistant's template (Web-to-Case Sample) and customize it.

Create one or more case queues on the Queues page in Setup to assign incoming cases.
Decide who will own cases created using the web form.

On the Case Assignment Rules page, create and activate an assignment rule to determine how web-generated cases are assigned to users or queues.
On the Support Settings page, select a user or queue as the Default Case Owner for cases that don't meet your criteria.
title: Setting up Web-to-Case in Service Cloud
